    <help><![CDATA[
spaCy Language Models Data Manager
===================================

This data manager downloads and installs spaCy language models for use with
the spaCy NLP annotation tool.

Available Models
----------------

spaCy provides trained pipeline models in different sizes:

- **sm (small)**: Fast, less accurate, ~10-20MB
- **md (medium)**: Balanced performance, includes word vectors, ~40-50MB
- **lg (large)**: Most accurate, large word vectors, ~500MB-800MB
- **trf (transformer)**: Transformer-based models, highest accuracy, ~400MB-500MB

Supported Languages
-------------------

Models are available for 23 languages:

- English, Spanish, German, French
- Chinese, Japanese, Korean
- Portuguese, Italian, Dutch
- Greek, Polish, Norwegian
- Lithuanian, Danish, Swedish
- Romanian, Catalan, Finnish
- Croatian, Macedonian
- Russian, Ukrainian

Usage
-----

1. Select one or more models you want to install (checkboxes)
2. Run the data manager
3. Each model is downloaded as a wheel from the explosion/spacy-models GitHub releases,
   its model data directory is extracted, and Galaxy moves it into the managed store and
   registers it in the data table (no pip install of the model package is performed)

Model sizes vary significantly. Small models download quickly, while large
and transformer models may take several minutes. Downloading multiple models
will take longer accordingly.

Version
-------

This data manager installs models compatible with spaCy version 3.8.11.

For more information about spaCy models, see: https://spacy.io/usage/models
    ]]></help>
